- `SUMPRODUCT` returns the matching value (or 0 if no match).

We will write this formula into every cell of columnâŊL from rowâŊ2 to the last row (rowâŊ22). After saving, we will call `recalculate()` to evaluate the formulas, then reload the workbook with `data_only=True` and print the newly computed values to verify they are not `None`.
